Part I - Ford Go Bike Trip¶

by Olumide Ogunyemi¶

Introduction¶

This data set includes information about individual rides made in a bike-sharing system covering the greater San Francisco Bay area.

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

There are 174952 samples in the dataset with 16 features. Most of the data are interger and objects(strings).

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

I am interested in determining set of people who make use of the bike the most.

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

I expect user type, member gender and member birth year to have the strongest effect in determing the type of people who ride the bike the most.

Discuss the distribution(s) of your variable(s) of interest. Were there any unusual points? Did you need to perform any transformations?¶

There are a lot of subscribers to the riding services and mojority of the riders are male.

Of the features you investigated, were there any unusual distributions? Did you perform any operations on the data to tidy, adjust, or change the form of the data? If so, why did you do this?¶

There are some outliers in member birth year which was dropped so that we can have a clearer view of the dataset. The user type was divided by subscriber and customers so that i can check the distribution of gender per customer and subsciber.

Conclusions¶

The majority of the riders are Male Adults between the birth year of 1979 to 1996. The Bike ride is mostly used by user between the birth year of 1979 to 1996 given that they have the duration per sec.

The duration of ride is determine by the age of the users in all category.
